FBIS3-48002 "dreas014_d_94020" FBIS-EAS-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 South Korea DPRK Delegation Reportedly Visits PRC SEZ SK2101083394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0752 GMT 21 Jan 94 SK2101083394 Seoul YONHAP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Hong Kong, Jan. 21 (YONHAP) -- An 11-man North Korean delegation led by Hwang Chang-yop, a secretary of the Worker's Party Central Committee and chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly Foreign Affairs Committee, has spent the last three days in the special economic zone [SEZ] in Zhuhai, Guangdong Province, collecting information on Chinese economic reforms, a city official said Friday. The North Koreans arrived in the southwestern port on Wednesday and spent the following day touring factories in an industrial complex. Hwang expressed deep interest in industrial development in the area on meeting Zhuhai Party Committee Secretary and Mayor Liang Guangda, the Chinese official told YONHAP in a telephone interview. The North Koreans left the city early Friday with material on economic reforms, the official said. Beijing was trying to keep the visit secret in respect for Pyongyang's position. "The three-day visit to Zhuhai is noteworthy because of the status of Hwang Chang-yop," a Western diplomat in Hong Kong said. "It is interesting to see North Korea so interested in Chinese-style economic reform."
